 <br>
I think a lot of people fail to take a good look at history and see what it teaches us.  I see a distinct similarity in the systematic appeasement both Germany pre-WW2 and Iraq today face.  The regulations that were in place after the treaty at Versaille post-ww1 were completely ignored by Hitler.  That wasnt the worst though, the League of Nations (Old name for the UN) did nothing about, and therefore were faced with WW2.  <br>
<br>
In 1998 when Iraq kicked the UN inspectors out they sent a clear message that they no longer were goin to adhere to the regulations and restrictions set upon them.  Its taken the UN 5 years to respond to a breach in the agreement and terms of Iraq.  I wouldnt be the least bit surprised if Iraq has and uses WMD.  In a lot of ways it would serve the world right.  <br>
<br>
One of the reasons Hitler lost WW2 was because he didnt care to look back in history and learn.  Napoleon lost to the russians because he tried to invade during the winter.  Almost 150 years later Hitler tried the same thing with the same result.  With a policy of appeasement the UN allowed Saddam free reign to do whatever he willed.  <br>
<br>
For those of u that are anti-war I just want u to think about something here.  What happens when Saddam is nuclear capable with enough missles and warheads to threaten us and our allies?  Do u think he wont use em?  If he already has them this point is moot, but if he doesnt, and he is trying to get them, then I think the effort needs to be made to disarm him and his regime.  I dont want to appease him until he sends a message to the world Via using WMD.  <br>
<br>
Again , this is just my view and opinion.  <br>
<br>
