<br>
In 1986 Iraq broke yet another treaty and withdrew his country from OPEC. Legally Saudi, Omon, Kuwait (you know that little country he invaded for their oil), and France (from an earlier treaty he broke in 76) have the rights to the oil in Iraq.<br>
<br>
Dont know what oil we will be getting our hands on, but still find it funny that the uneducated on this subject still use this arguement.<br>
<br>
Someone on the boards said there was no way for Saddam to prove that he distroyed his weapons and weapon components. Well, thats not true either. Unfortunantly, most of the components used in these type weapons are unstable and have to be disposed of is very precise manners. Many calling for completely new equipment to be used ONLY for that destruction. Not to mention the fact that the waste from destroying those weapons would then have to be contained and measured to determine that they were now in a non-toxic form and the waste itself would be around (yes prolly buried somewhere) because it cannot be burned. So, to those saying you cant prove something is destroyed because it was destroyed need to do some reading.<br>
<br>
Why dont we go after every country that sells weapons of mass destruction to terrorists I saw asked a few times as well. The answer is simple. No other country sells the weapons. Yes other countries do sell the chemicals and solid materials needed for the weapons construction, but at the same time these same supplies can be used for other things.<br>
When a country manufactures and stockpiles these weapons and sells a few to make a little money on the side to the highest bidder, thats where the world is obligated to step in and stop it. <br>
<br>
But then we could do nothing and let them go thier own ways. That way it wont be an airplane leveling buildings and killing people next time, We could wait for Saddam to finish his nuclear program, sell it to the next terrorist org that has the funds and then play pin the tail on the Americans to see what city gets the big bang theory tested in thier backyard.<br>
<br>
Do I think we should go to war in needed to stop this. Hell yes! I'm not a war monger sitting in war paint beating a drum and chanting, but I am adult enough to know that there are some people in the world that cannot be reached through whatever amount of diplomacy is offered.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=557698">What Cobbin wears</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showMessageRange?topicID=2031.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showMessageRange?topicID=2031.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showMessageRange?topicID=2031.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showMessageRange?topicID=2031.topic&start=81&stop=84>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=2031.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showNextMessage?topicID=2031.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2031.topic&index=60><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.threadControl?topicID=2031.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2031.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.unsubscribeU